The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Wednesday, March 05, 2003 				 Veerbhadra 
																								Chandigarh, March 4: Veerbhadra Singh was today unanimously elected leader of the Congress Legislature Party in a prelude to his taking over as Himachal Pradesh chief minister, a post he has held four times earlier.																								Vidya Stokes, the state Congress president and rival for the post, was asked to propose Singhs name at the meeting. Sources close to Stokes said she has been promised a larger say in government functioning.
